# Garlicky Greens

> An adaptation of Alton Brown’s Vlad’s Very Garlicky Greens. #vegetarian #pasta

![](9D53D024-E78E-4B66-9A11-0B4D4A3BA25D.jpeg)

- Water |  | 
- Salt |  | 
- Linguine | 8 oz | 

Bring seasoned water in a large pot to a rolling boil. Add linguine.

- Olive Oil |  | 
- Garlic | 7 cloves | Minced

When pasta is about half-way done, start a pan over medium / medium-low heat, add oil and garlic and stir constantly.

- Spinach | 3 cups | 
- Salt | to taste | 

After garlic is soft and barely golden, add spinach and toss until slightly wilted. Season with salt.

Strain pasta, add to the pan, and stir to combine. Add more salt to taste.
